"{\"uid\": \"meetings.skift.com-2024-07-03-la-convention-center-expansion-approved-ahead-of-2028-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles is now on track to unveil a major convention center expansion, just in time for the LA28 Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999951805876, \"rank\": 3.827334552034972e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Select a question above orask something else  On Tuesday, the Los Angeles City Councilapprovedthe Los Angeles Convention Center (LACC) Expansion and Modernization Project.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Construction is planned to start in spring 2025 and be completed before the 2028 Olympic and Paralympic Games start.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The City of Los Angeles owns the LACC, which is managed byASM Global.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LACC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The venue hosts almost 200 meetings and events and attracts 2 million visitors annually.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The expansion includes adding 190,000 square feet to connect the South and West Exhibit Halls, creating one contiguous hall.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will also add 55,000 square feet of new meeting room space and 95,000 square feet of multipurpose space.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The plan also features a redesign of Gilbert Lindsay Plaza, introducing public open space and an outdoor event venue.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gilbert Lindsay\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The L.A. City Council projects that the expansion will create 7,445 jobs during construction and 2,147 ongoing jobs.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999998060503, \"rank\": 1.9043442982777324e-10, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"score\": 0.9998901221995404, \"rank\": 7.618198468256291e-05, \"text\": \"City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once concluded, projections point to the expansion generating $165 million in additional revenue from the 50,000 additional attendee days annually, equating to an increase of $30 million ($570 million over 30 years) to the city's general fund tax revenue.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a jointstatementfrom the Los Angeles City Tourism Department, the Los Angeles Convention Center and the Los Angeles Tourism & Convention Board, the city acknowledges its current competitive disadvantage.\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angeles City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Convention Center\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Los Angeles has been at a competitive disadvantage in attracting large, citywide conventions due to the lack of contiguous space, especially as competitors have completed or are in the process of completing major expansions.\\\"\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999951805876, \"rank\": 3.827334552034972e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Council has selected a public-private partnership model, also referred to as P3, which incorporates designing, building, financing, operating, and maintaining in one model.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"score\": 0.44388821931287126, \"rank\": 0.7651794541017118, \"text\": \"P3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This model involves contracting with a joint venture of AEG and The Plenary Group.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1953, \"end\": 1956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Plenary Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The P3 model was selected over a \\\"construction manager at risk\\\" model, which would have been financed entirely by the City of Los Angeles through city-issued long-term debt.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"score\": 0.44388821931287126, \"rank\": 0.7651794541017118, \"text\": \"P3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rejected model would have delayed development by six months, making using the LACC during the LA28 Games impossible.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LACC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, operating costs were projected to be approximately $5 million less annually.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In October, LA Tourism formed aunique partnershipwith AEG, a sister company to ASM Global.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2417, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467893427621576e-42, \"text\": \"ASM Global\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city recently secured $709.9 million infederal fundingfor infrastructure improvements in preparation for the LA28 Games.\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:AEG,ASM Global,convention center,expansion,Los Angeles,Los Angeles Convention Center,Olympics  The Los Angeles City Council has approved a major expansion and modernization project for the LA Convention Center, set to be completed before the 2028 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2585, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 2589, \"end\": 2599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467893427621576e-42, \"text\": \"ASM Global\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999951805876, \"rank\": 3.827334552034972e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2640, \"end\": 2669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Convention Center\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 2684, \"end\": 2708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.345500785683836e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LA Convention Center\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project will create over 7,000 construction jobs and generate $165 million in additional revenue annually.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A public-private partnership model, involving AEG and The Plenary Group, was selected to manage the expansion.\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 3068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3004, \"end\": 3007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Plenary Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\"}]}]}"